-- Serbia to Seek Adviser for Preparing Shale Oil Tender, Beta Says
-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 2012-01-03T12:52:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-03/serbia-to-seek-adviser-for-preparing-shale-oil-tender-beta-says.html
Serbia will invite offers later this
month for an adviser to help the country prepare a tender for
exploration and use of its shale oil reserves,  Beta   news agency 
reported, citing Mining and Environment Minister Oliver Dulic.  The adviser will help define terms under which Serbia will
seek a strategic partner for the investment estimated at between
700 million euros ($912 million) and 800 million euros, the
report quoted Dulic as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
